<p>
  <span class="nym">Griselda</span>
  <span class="gen">f.</span>
  
  <span class="etym">Possibly <span class="lang">Proto-Germanic</span> <i>*grēwaz</i> 'grey' + <span class="lang">Old High German</span> <i>hiltja</i> 'battle'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>The character of "Patient Griselda" occurs in both Petrarch and Chaucer, as well as other, less-well known, literature, and her popularity contributed to the use of the name in the later period.</p>
</div>
  


